{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b25bfe60-b5be-4a04-9d9c-9261436f20d7","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1e0d0ec7-6ea1-4cf2-bfe1-08e5ea0b46a9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test skip/ignore attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":303,"requestId":"4C17:3362F9:B820FA:E3D4A2:6A012D4F"},"id":"2b357791-6596-4704-b712-2f809c7e3686","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:13:57.837Z","parentId":"51442e16-3aa2-4014-97ae-0f533de5bd7f"}
